1307	// bindSourceToPeer records addr→p in the source-demux map, installed lock-free by a CAS
1308	// republish of a copy with the entry added (T88). It takes NO lock: a reader must never block
1309	// on m.mu (Close waits on the readers WHILE holding m.mu), so the binding — written from a
1310	// readLoop goroutine — must not acquire it. Idempotent: an already-present addr→p binding is a
1311	// no-op, and a lost CAS (a concurrent bind on another socket) simply retries. Copy-on-write
1312	// keeps every published map immutable, so a concurrent lookupPeerBySource over the old snapshot
1313	// is never disturbed.
1314	//
1315	// It returns true when addr is bound to p on return (either freshly installed, already present,
1316	// or re-pointed from another peer — a roam, T90) and false ONLY when the map is at its
1317	// maxDemuxSources cap and addr is a NEW source: drop-on-exhaustion (Q26/Q27). A cap-drop NEVER
1318	// evicts an existing binding, so a live peer is never disturbed by a bootstrap flood; only a
1319	// brand-new source's bootstrap is (temporarily) refused, and WG retransmits cover the gap once
1320	// a slot frees (e.g. a dead peer's teardown). Re-pointing or re-affirming an already-present
